{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d0fffdb3-d6d9-4894-a3d9-3c894a0fc686","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passed/failed, so you can track them in test results.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c03fd436-acfc-44c2-81bb-505cd3bfae9b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework attributes. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":319,"requestId":"4811:FD676:759710:87E344:69FBE703"},"id":"d98d22ee-b865-435a-be8b-1693687ea976","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:12:43.447Z","parentId":"e7aefaab-226c-4741-b80f-b74042f1d0be"}
